<br>
I still return home to visit once in a while, and I will not hunt in Tunare's realm, but the actions of the church have made me realize how tenuous is the distinction between &quot;good&quot; and &quot;evil&quot;.<br>
<br>
So I'm a little bitter, having realized that life is not black and white, but I still try to be &quot;good&quot; in my own secular way, and make no judgements of others based on their race or religion - until they prove themselves untrustworthy. For all I know, they have been as brainwashed as I was.<br>
<br>
I think Tunare will be asking some hard questions of  certain members of the Felwithe priesthood come Reckoning Day. <p>Gwynne Athelas<br>
